values:
After last week's marathon to make G3 perfect in every evil little picky pre-press detail, <lj-cut text="I got real interested in Photoshop automation, and I thought I&#39;d share:">I got real interested in Photoshop automation, and I thought I'd share:

Here's some Javascript that will automatically output a tiff that is to ka-blam.com's specs. It does the following stuff:
<ol><li>hides any layers that have NOEXPORT in their names (I use this to automatically turn off the ka-blam template)</li>
<li>sets the compression to LZW and turns off layer output</li>
<li>aborts with an error if the dimensions are not 3150x2100</li>
<li>aborts with an error if the color mode is not RGB</li>
<li>aborts with an error if the resolution is not 300DPI</li>
<li>saves out a tiff as a copy in the same directory as the original file</li>
<li>restores the visibility of any NOEXPORT layers it hid</li></ol>
You can save it off and run it by selecting File &gt; Scripts &gt; Browse and selecting it. On CS3, you can drop it in the presets/scripts directory and it'll appear in the Scripts submenu automatically next time you restart PS.

I have no idea if this works on anything but the Mac version of CS3, but I hope it'll be useful to someone. I wish I'd taken an evening to write this last week!

<table border="1" cellpadding="5"><tr><td><pre>var doc = app.activeDocument;

var saveState = saveState(doc);
tiffsave(doc);
restoreState(saveState);

function restoreState( saveState ) {
    // restore the visibility of all layers.
    for (var l in saveState) {
        saveState[l].layer.visible = saveState[l].visible;
    }
}

function saveState(doc) {
    var saveState = new Array();
    for (var i = 0; i &lt; doc.artLayers.length; i++) {
        var l=doc.artLayers[i];
        if ( l.name.match(/NOEXPORT/)) {
            var stateHash = new Object();
            stateHash.layer = l;
            stateHash.visible = l.visible;
            saveState[l.name]= stateHash;
            l.visible=false;
        }
    }
    return saveState;
}

function tiffsave(doc) { 

    // resolutions and dimensions

    var r = doc.resolution;

    if ( r != 300 ) {
        alert("bad resolution (" + r + " DPI)\naborting save!");
        return;
    }

    var w = doc.width.as('px');
    var h = doc.height.as('px');
    if ( ( w != '2100' ) || (  h != '3150' )  )  {
        alert("bad document dimensions (" + w + "x" + h +')\naborting save');
        return;
    }

    // set mode right.

    if ( doc.mode != DocumentMode.RGB ) {
        alert("document mode is not RGB, aborting save.");
        return;
    }

    var so = new TiffSaveOptions();
    so.imageCompression = TIFFEncoding.TIFFLZW;
    so.layers = false;

    // destination

    var file  = doc.fullName;
    var dest = file.fullName;
    var fileSpec = new File(dest);

    doc.saveAs( fileSpec, so, true);


}</pre></td></tr></table></lj-cut>
